And the issue we are facing with our security server (as below) is unable to initialize the database schema, please find below screenshots for the version installed and the error message which pops up when the SA console is opened. Hello Leela,

Frantz is currently out of the office so I included a scheduling link below for performing a preflight.

https://nwxcorp.my.salesforce-sites.com/cts?Id=B8T3R9sIIQ6rLG1_BzaGZEIBg5rdV6QWo3pJ2KyN06U-Z&MeetingID=AqgwrYfMWncwno6mnLxJR4engFcqZF3tKHWcOUvwSsI-Z


I also wanted to inquire is the security server where you are receiving the database schema error using the same database as the recently upgraded StealthAUDIT 11.5 instance? That would explain the error message as they would have different database schemas and running different versions against the same database would not be supported.

If both consoles are on the same build, could you please zip up the "<drive>Program Files (x86)STEALTHbitsStealthAUDITSADatabaseLogsApplication" folder and attach to the ticket.


Regards,

TextBody:
Thanks again to both of your for your time during our meeting today.

In reviewing the error occurring when attempting to schedule jobs in StealthAUDIT, we found that the local security policy "Network access: Do not allow storage of passwords and credentials for network authentication " is enabled and would be the most likely cause for the error. We were able to reproduce the same error message outside of the StealthAUDIT console by creating a scheduled task and attempting to configure to allow the task to run whether the user is logged on or not.

We also observed that historically, scheduled tasks were failing due to a credential error which is caused by this security policy setting not allowing the storage of credentials.

For reference, the following Microsoft discussion outlines the above behavior.

Task Scheduler Error “A specified logon session does not exist”


Please use the link below to schedule a meeting for the preflight of the next console upgrade.

https://nwxcorp.my.salesforce-sites.com/cts?Id=7YfX.UFmE5y.e2FlpSztks8FviuODjwCpT.Afb38cf8-Z&MeetingID=adLFAUZT5RqYmeZwWgbMNR.cR2PJCYirv8V._nS45UE-Z


Regards,

Kurt Gerth

Thanks again to both of your for your time during our meeting today.

In reviewing the error occurring when attempting to schedule jobs in StealthAUDIT, we found that the local security policy "Network access: Do not allow storage of passwords and credentials for network authentication " is enabled and would be the most likely cause for the error. We were able to reproduce the same error message outside of the StealthAUDIT console by creating a scheduled task and attempting to configure to allow the task to run whether the user is logged on or not.

We also observed that historically, scheduled tasks were failing due to a credential error which is caused by this security policy setting not allowing the storage of credentials.

For reference, the following Microsoft discussion outlines the above behavior.

Task Scheduler Error “A specified logon session does not exist”


Please use the link below to schedule a meeting for the preflight of the next console upgrade.

Thanks again to both of your for your time during our meeting today.

In reviewing the error occurring when attempting to schedule jobs in StealthAUDIT, we found that the local security policy "Network access: Do not allow storage of passwords and credentials for network authentication " is enabled and would be the most likely cause for the error. We were able to reproduce the same error message outside of the StealthAUDIT console by creating a scheduled task and attempting to configure to allow the task to run whether the user is logged on or not.

We also observed that historically, scheduled tasks were failing due to a credential error which is caused by this security policy setting not allowing the storage of credentials.

For reference, the following Microsoft discussion outlines the above behavior.

Task Scheduler Error “A specified logon session does not exist”<https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/ask-the-performance-team/task-scheduler-error-8220-a-specified-logon-session-does-not/ba-p/375056>

Thanks again to both of your for your time during our meeting today.

In reviewing the error occurring when attempting to schedule jobs in StealthAUDIT, we found that the local security policy "Network access: Do not allow storage of passwords and credentials for network authentication " is enabled and would be the most likely cause for the error. We were able to reproduce the same error message outside of the StealthAUDIT console by creating a scheduled task and attempting to configure to allow the task to run whether the user is logged on or not.

We also observed that historically, scheduled tasks were failing due to a credential error which is caused by this security policy setting not allowing the storage of credentials.

For reference, the following Microsoft discussion outlines the above behavior.

Task Scheduler Error “A specified logon session does not exist”<https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/ask-the-performance-team/task-scheduler-error-8220-a-specified-logon-session-does-not/ba-p/375056>

Thanks again to both of your for your time during our meeting today.

In reviewing the error occurring when attempting to schedule jobs in StealthAUDIT, we found that the local security policy "Network access: Do not allow storage of passwords and credentials for network authentication " is enabled and would be the most likely cause for the error. We were able to reproduce the same error message outside of the StealthAUDIT console by creating a scheduled task and attempting to configure to allow the task to run whether the user is logged on or not.

We also observed that historically, scheduled tasks were failing due to a credential error which is caused by this security policy setting not allowing the storage of credentials.

For reference, the following Microsoft discussion outlines the above behavior.

Task Scheduler Error “A specified logon session does not exist”


Please use the link below to schedule a meeting for the preflight of the next console upgrade.

Thanks again to both of your for your time during our meeting today.

In reviewing the error occurring when attempting to schedule jobs in StealthAUDIT, we found that the local security policy "Network access: Do not allow storage of passwords and credentials for network authentication " is enabled and would be the most likely cause for the error. We were able to reproduce the same error message outside of the StealthAUDIT console by creating a scheduled task and attempting to configure to allow the task to run whether the user is logged on or not.

We also observed that historically, scheduled tasks were failing due to a credential error which is caused by this security policy setting not allowing the storage of credentials.

For reference, the following Microsoft discussion outlines the above behavior.

Task Scheduler Error “A specified logon session does not exist”<https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/ask-the-performance-team/task-scheduler-error-8220-a-specified-logon-session-does-not/ba-p/375056>

Thanks again to both of your for your time during our meeting today.

In reviewing the error occurring when attempting to schedule jobs in StealthAUDIT, we found that the local security policy "Network access: Do not allow storage of passwords and credentials for network authentication " is enabled and would be the most likely cause for the error. We were able to reproduce the same error message outside of the StealthAUDIT console by creating a scheduled task and attempting to configure to allow the task to run whether the user is logged on or not.

We also observed that historically, scheduled tasks were failing due to a credential error which is caused by this security policy setting not allowing the storage of credentials.

For reference, the following Microsoft discussion outlines the above behavior.

Task Scheduler Error “A specified logon session does not exist”<https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/ask-the-performance-team/task-scheduler-error-8220-a-specified-logon-session-does-not/ba-p/375056>


Please use the link below to schedule a meeting for the preflight of the next console upgrade.

In reviewing the error occurring when attempting to schedule jobs in StealthAUDIT, we found that the local security policy "Network access: Do not allow storage of passwords and credentials for network authentication " is enabled and would be the most likely cause for the error. We were able to reproduce the same error message outside of the StealthAUDIT console by creating a scheduled task and attempting to configure to allow the task to run whether the user is logged on or not.

We also observed that historically, scheduled tasks were failing due to a credential error which is caused by this security policy setting not allowing the storage of credentials.

For reference, the following Microsoft discussion outlines the above behavior.

Task Scheduler Error “A specified logon session does not exist”


Please use the link below to schedule a meeting for the preflight of the next console upgrade.

Thanks again to both of your for your time during our meeting today.

In reviewing the error occurring when attempting to schedule jobs in StealthAUDIT, we found that the local security policy "Network access: Do not allow storage of passwords and credentials for network authentication " is enabled and would be the most likely cause for the error. We were able to reproduce the same error message outside of the StealthAUDIT console by creating a scheduled task and attempting to configure to allow the task to run whether the user is logged on or not.

We also observed that historically, scheduled tasks were failing due to a credential error which is caused by this security policy setting not allowing the storage of credentials.

For reference, the following Microsoft discussion outlines the above behavior.

Task Scheduler Error "A specified logon session does not exist"<https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/ask-the-performance-team/task-scheduler-error-8220-a-specified-logon-session-does-not/ba-p/375056>

Thanks again to both of your for your time during our meeting today.

In reviewing the error occurring when attempting to schedule jobs in StealthAUDIT, we found that the local security policy "Network access: Do not allow storage of passwords and credentials for network authentication " is enabled and would be the most likely cause for the error. We were able to reproduce the same error message outside of the StealthAUDIT console by creating a scheduled task and attempting to configure to allow the task to run whether the user is logged on or not.

We also observed that historically, scheduled tasks were failing due to a credential error which is caused by this security policy setting not allowing the storage of credentials.

For reference, the following Microsoft discussion outlines the above behavior.

Task Scheduler Error “A specified logon session does not exist”

Thanks again to both of your for your time during our meeting today.

In reviewing the error occurring when attempting to schedule jobs in StealthAUDIT, we found that the local security policy "Network access: Do not allow storage of passwords and credentials for network authentication " is enabled and would be the most likely cause for the error. We were able to reproduce the same error message outside of the StealthAUDIT console by creating a scheduled task and attempting to configure to allow the task to run whether the user is logged on or not.

We also observed that historically, scheduled tasks were failing due to a credential error which is caused by this security policy setting not allowing the storage of credentials.

For reference, the following Microsoft discussion outlines the above behavior.

Task Scheduler Error “A specified logon session does not exist”<https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/ask-the-performance-team/task-scheduler-error-8220-a-specified-logon-session-does-not/ba-p/375056>
